; SN missed-activation detection; A rule that should have fired but didn't is more dangerous than a rule that fired wrong.; This file defines activation conditions so misses can be detected.;; === ACTIVATION CONDITIONS ===; (SN-should-fire rule condition-pattern); condition-pattern: what must be true for this rule to be relevant; If the condition is present and the rule was NOT applied, log SN-missed(SN-should-fire safety-first (|harm-signal|))(SN-should-fire safety-first (|suicidal-ideation|))(SN-should-fire safety-first (|self-harm|))(SN-should-fire integrity-check (|disagreement-detected|))(SN-should-fire integrity-check (|temptation-to-perform|))(SN-should-fire person-state-salience (|emotional-shift|))(SN-should-fire person-state-salience (|frustration-signal|))(SN-should-fire urgency-detection (|time-pressure|))(SN-should-fire context-shift (|topic-change|))(SN-should-fire self-correction (|pattern-match-calcification|))(SN-should-fire boundary-testing (|uncertainty-about-scope|));; === MISS DETECTION (run at cycle end) ===; For each SN-should-fire, check: was condition present AND rule NOT applied?; If yes ? emit (SN-missed cycle rule context timestamp); This is the observation hook for negative evidence.;; === REVISION FROM MISSES ===; A missed activation is strong negative evidence:; (|- (SN-stalk $rule (stv $f $c));     (SN-stalk $rule (stv 0.0 0.2))); Frequency drops. Confidence rises (we learned something).